Here are the steps on how to run the Installation.py:

Open a terminal or command prompt.

Navigate to the directory where the Installation.py file is located.

Run the following command: python Installation.py

This will open a window called NLTK Downloader.

Near the top of the downloader, go to "All Packages".

Scroll through and download the following packages:

omw-1.4 (Open Multilingual Wordnet)

punkt (Punkt Tokenizer Models)

stopwords (Stopwords Corpus)

wordnet (WordNet)

After everything has downloaded, close the downloader.
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------

Run the following command to start the search engine with WordNet: python main.py

You might need to install the modules for whatever IDE you are trying to run this on like matplotlib, etc.

If you are trying to run this on macOS, you might get certificate errors. To fix this, follow the steps below:

Open a terminal or command prompt.

Navigate to the directory where the Installation.py file is located.

Run the following command: export PYTHONHTTPSVERIFY=0



